%kkgpoisson 'Generate Poisson Noise Data'
% This MatLab function was automatically generated by a converter (KhorosToMatLab) from the Khoros kgpoisson.pane file
%
% Parameters: 
% Integer: wsize 'Width ', default: 512: 'Width size of noise value data'
% Integer: hsize 'Height ', default: 512: 'Height size of noise value data'
% Integer: dsize 'Depth ', default: 1: 'Depth size of noise value data'
% Integer: tsize 'Time ', default: 1: 'Time size of noise value data'
% Integer: esize 'Elements ', default: 1: 'Element dimension size of noise data'
% OutputFile: o 'Output File', required: 'Output file containing noise data'
%
% Example: o = kkgpoisson( {'wsize',512;'hsize',512;'dsize',1;'tsize',1;'esize',1;'o',''})
%
% Khoros helpfile follows below:
%
%  PROGRAM
% kgpoisson - Generate Poisson Noise Data
%
%  DESCRIPTION
% "kgpoisson" generates Poisson noise of the specified parameters in the
% output data object (-o). The amount of time (-ptime) and variance (-pvar) must 
% be specified for the Poisson distribution to be generated.
% 
% The size of all five dimensions of the object can be specified. The data type
% of the output object can also be specified. "kgpoisson" can also generate
% complex valued Poisson noise data.
%
%  
%
%  EXAMPLES
%
%  "SEE ALSO"
% DATAMANIP::kgnoise, DATAMANIP::kgexpon, DATAMANIP::kggauss, 
% DATAMANIP::kgrayleigh, DATAMANIP::kguniform
%
%  RESTRICTIONS 
%
%  REFERENCES 
%
